This project is a comprehensive desktop application for managing various aspects of a hospital or healthcare center. Built using Java and NetBeans IDE, the system offers a user-friendly interface for managing patient records, appointments, billing, and hospital staff administration.

Patient Management: Register new patients, update records, and maintain medical history.
Appointment Scheduling: Schedule patient appointments with doctors and manage availability.
Billing and Invoicing: Generate bills for services and keep track of payments.
Doctor and Staff Management: Maintain records of doctors, nurses, and administrative staff.
Inventory Management: Manage hospital inventory and supplies efficiently.
Reports and Analytics: Generate reports for patient statistics, revenue, and more.


Java: Core programming language for backend logic and GUI development.
NetBeans IDE: Integrated development environment for Java development.
Swing: Java's GUI toolkit used for building the user interface.
MySQL: Database management system for storing and retrieving data.

Installation and Usage
Clone the repository:
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/hospital-management-system.git
Open the project in NetBeans IDE.
Set up MySQL database using provided SQL scripts.
Build and run the project.
